{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"022b7ca8-d731-4d3d-9612-0349ce34ef83","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory. Since this is a general question rather than a repo-specific change, here's what you need to do:\n\n### Switch to NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. On nuget.org** — configure a Trusted Publisher:\n- Go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted publishers**\n- Add a GitHub Actions publisher: set **repository owner**, **repo name**, **workflow filename**, and optionally an **environment**\n\n**2. In your workflow** — replace the API key approach:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    # Required for OIDC token\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n    # Optional but recommended: lock to a GitHub Environment\n    environment: nuget-publish\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # Trusted publishing — no API key needed\n      - uses: dotnet/nuget-push@v1\n        with:\n          source: https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` in `dotnet nuget push --api-key` | No secret needed |\n| No `permissions` block | Add `id-token: write` |\n| — | Use `dotnet/nuget-push` action (handles OIDC token exchange) |\n\n**3. Clean up** — remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once verified.\n\nWould you like me to look at a specific workflow file to make the changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a78adbac-bcc1-45af-a14a-b3a4e5138ac7","outputTokens":432,"requestId":"1C15:13B160:5C6CC82:63E5644:69FBE2B7"},"id":"284057a3-dba7-4676-80a5-79146cee626b","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:54:25.520Z","parentId":"4e46c581-f17e-4ea0-9e1b-396653be15fc"}
